 Snider Jr., director of the division of tuberculosis control at the Centers for Disease Control in Atlanta.
 In parts of Africa, where AIDS is already a health risk, tuberculosis has become epidemic, said Dr.
 Untreated, tuberculosis kills about 50 percent of its victims within two years, according to the Centers for Disease Control.
 However, he noted that there had been an increase in positive TB tests among AIDS health workers.
 Tuberculosis can be effectively treated, even in AIDS patients, underscoring efforts to screen persons for the disease, the doctor said.
